reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Looks Great - Easy to Assemble - Great Price
reviews.reviewText: I was skeptical about buying, but after recieving it and then assembling the model- yeah, definitely glad I made the purchase. It looks great. It doesn't look cheap, and it doesn't feel cheap. The rods and frames are actually metal and not plastic, so that's quality. As for assembling? One of the easiest product I've ever had to assemble. Took me probably less than 10 minutes, and I'm no genius when it comes to buidling anything. Lastly, I did buy this during Cyber Monday, but honestly the full price for it is more than fair I'd say. I do wish it was just a bit larger, but eh not the end of the world. I reckon I'll be keeping this little stand for many years.

reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Have real tools handy…
reviews.reviewText: Went together quickly (almost) and seem sturdy for what they are. Got to the very last step on the second table and their pre-drilled holes in the metal don’t line up with the holes in the wood at all. Husband has to drill new holes to make them functional. Also the little “shelf” right below the top is made of fabric, in case others didn’t notice in the description as I didn’t…

reviews.reviewText: These are great tables. Love the height. My bed is tall and these are perfect. The 2nd shelf is cloth but very tight. Bottom shelf is mesh. This was easy to put together. Just wish the top was a bit bigger
